title: The Art Institute of Chicago Pocket Guide
description:
The Pocket Guide highlights 132 favorite and notable objects from the Art Institute’s permanent collection. Its handy, easy-to-use format is designed to help you explore works from around the world that span thousands of years. These range from ancient Chinese bronzes to iconic Impressionist paintings and African masks to photography and modern art. The Pocket Guide can help make your visit more meaningful and also serves as a perfect souvenir of one of America’s great museums.

  • Size:  4.25 in. x 8.5 in. 
  • Softcover
  • 72 pages
  • 132 color images
